<p>I need to send a batch of files in a FTP through a clustered WSO2 ESB environment, including 1 manager node and 2 worker nodes. However, the manager node always unexpected participates in file process, and result in a fault afterwards. Therefore, I want to pinned the proxy to the two workers, but the pinnedServers parameter doesn't work. I want to know if there is a way to separately disable the manager's VFS function, or make the pinnedServers parameter work in a VFS clustering environment. </p>  <p>My configuration is shown below.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;proxy xmlns="http://ws.apache.org/ns/synapse"        name="PS_TEST_VFS"        transports="vfs"        statistics="disable"        trace="enable"        startOnLoad="true"        pinnedServers="server.server1"&gt;    &lt;target&gt;       &lt;inSequence&gt;          ......       &lt;/inSequence&gt;       &lt;outSequence&gt;          ......       &lt;/outSequence&gt;       &lt;faultSequence&gt;         ......       &lt;/faultSequence&gt;    &lt;/target&gt;    &lt;parameter name="transport.vfs.FileProcessInterval"&gt;1&lt;/parameter&gt;    &lt;parameter name="transport.PollInterval"&gt;5&lt;/parameter&gt;    &lt;parameter name="transport.vfs.FileURI"&gt;ftp://username:password@xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx/Outbound?vfs.passive=true&lt;/parameter&gt;    &lt;parameter name="transport.vfs.FileNamePattern"&gt;.*\.json&lt;/parameter&gt;    &lt;parameter name="transport.vfs.ContentType"&gt;application/json&lt;/parameter&gt;    &lt;description/&gt; &lt;/proxy&gt; </code></pre>